Background — pipeline contract
═══════════════════════════════════════════════

The `fpd-cohort` report handler lives at `reports/FpdCohort.ahk` in the Bravo Data Extraction project. It runs the saved Bravo report "Claude First Payment Default" via the standard Loans/Buys → Custom Reports → Choose Saved Report → Ok flow, reads the count from the title bar, enables the summary panel to read the $ sum, and writes one CSV row per store with columns: `store, date, count, dollar_sum`.

If the metric definition needs to change (different cohort window, different filter), edit the saved Bravo report itself — the watcher handler is metric-agnostic.

